What does the "rect" function do?
The "rect" function draws rectangles. It provies the coordinates of the shape.

What does the "rectMode" function do?
The "rectMode" function adapts, alters, and adjusts the area from which rectangles are composed in.
The function identifies the x and y values, which identify a certain point to alter.

What is a pixel?
A baisic unit of programable color on a computer display or image. 
A pixel's size strongly depends on what the set resolution of the display is.

What is HSB?
HSB= hue,saturation, brightness. 
Color is defined by three numbers, the values range form 0 to 360.
